    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Grate your <strong>white cup mushrooms</strong></p><p>Chop your <strong>chestnut mushrooms </strong>roughly</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>brown onion[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mother-of-all-veggie-lasagnes-with-mushroom-and-truffled-breadcrumbs/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>over a high heat</p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>chopped mushrooms</strong> to the pan and cook for 5-6 min or until browned all over</p><p>Once browned all over, reduce the heat to medium and add the <strong>sliced onion </strong>and <strong>grated mushrooms </strong>and cook for a further 3-4 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mother-of-all-veggie-lasagnes-with-mushroom-and-truffled-breadcrumbs/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, melt 20g <span class=\"text-purple\">[30g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span> <strong>butter</strong> in a pot over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add 20g <span class=\"text-purple\">[30g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1-2 min or until a sandy paste forms \u2013 this is your roux</p><p>Add 250ml<span class=\"text-purple\"> [375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>milk</strong> gradually and whisk for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains</p><p>Remove from the heat, season with a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong> and stir \u2013 this is your <strong>b\u00e9chamel</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mother-of-all-veggie-lasagnes-with-mushroom-and-truffled-breadcrumbs/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>soft cheese </strong>and 1/3 of your <strong>grated Italian hard cheese </strong>(you'll use the rest later) to the <strong>b\u00e9chamel </strong>and mix until fully combined \u2013 this is your <strong>cheesy</strong> <strong>b\u00e9chamel</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mother-of-all-veggie-lasagnes-with-mushroom-and-truffled-breadcrumbs/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong>, your <strong>dried oregano </strong>and your<strong> vegetable stock mix </strong>to the pan with the mushrooms and cook for 1-2 min further</p><p>Add your <strong>soy sauce </strong>and give everything a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>mushroom filling</strong></p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mother-of-all-veggie-lasagnes-with-mushroom-and-truffled-breadcrumbs/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Layer some of the <strong>mushroom filling </strong>over the bottom of an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong>, then top with 3 <strong>lasagne sheets</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>remaining mushroom filling </strong>on top, then spread 1/3 of the <strong>cheesy b\u00e9chamel </strong>on top</p><p>Layer with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lasagne sheets </strong>and top with the <strong>remaining cheesy b\u00e9chamel</strong>, ensuring all of the pasta is covered</p><p>Cover with <strong>tin foil</strong> and cook in the oven for 20-25 min or until the pasta is cooked</p><p>Tip: You may need to layer differently depending on the size of your dish!</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mother-of-all-veggie-lasagnes-with-mushroom-and-truffled-breadcrumbs/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>While the lasagne is cooking, add your <strong>panko breadcrumbs </strong>to a small bowl with the <strong>remaining grated Italian hard cheese</strong>, a small pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and a generous grind of <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Add a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>to the bowl and mix it all together \u2013 these are your <strong>cheesy breadcrumbs</strong></p><p>Once the pasta is cooked, remove the dish from the oven and discard the tin foil</p><p>Top the lasagne with the <strong>cheesy breadcrumbs</strong>, return to the oven and cook for a further 5 min or until golden \u2013 this is your <strong>mushroom</strong> <strong>lasagne</strong> <strong>with</strong> <strong>cheesy</strong> <strong>breadcrumbs</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/mother-of-all-veggie-lasagnes-with-mushroom-and-truffled-breadcrumbs/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>mushroom</strong> <strong>lasagne</strong> <strong>with</strong> <strong>cheesy</strong> <strong>breadcrumbs</strong> with your <strong>truffle oil </strong>drizzled over the top</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
